ed since 1966. Due to the condition of the tower (which was suffering from concrete cancer making it structurally unsafe), the tower was demolished in February 2018.<ref>https://www.railwaymagazine.co.uk/7488/december-2018/ Railway Magazine article on Immingham coal tower</ref>\n\n===United States===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Place Name\n!State\n!Railroad\n!Year Built\n!Type\n!Capacity (tons)\n!Builder\n!Remarks\n!Coordinates\n|-\n|[[Flomaton, Alabama|Flomaton]]\n|[[Alabama]]\n|[[Louisville and Nashville Railroad]]\n|1943\n|Coaling tower\n|\n|\n|Active tracks, similar to Decatur and Oneonta\n|align=right|{{coord|31.00016|-87.25065|format=dms}}\n|-\n|[[Montgomery, Alabama|Montgomery]]<ref name=\"books.google.com\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/al1290.sheet.00014a/|title=Coaling Tower Elevations - Western Railway of Alabama Montgomery Rail Shops, 701 North Perry Street, Montgomery, Montgomery County, AL; HAER AL-186 (sheet 14 of 14)|last=Dubin|first=Elisabeth|date=1999|website=Library of Congress, Prints & Photographs Online Catalog|publisher=National Park Service, United States Department of the Interior|access-date=27 June 2016}}</ref>\n|[[Alabama]]\n|[[Western Railway of Alabama]]\n|1913\n|Coaling tower\n|600\n|[[Thompson\u2013Starrett Co.|Roberts & Schaefer Company]]\n|Abandoned, Chester Yard\n|align=right|{{coord|32.39166|-86.30757|format=dms}}\n|-\n|[[Opelika, Alabama|Opelika]]\n|[[Alabama]]\n|[[Western Railway of Alabama]]\n|\n|Coaling tower\n|\n|\n|Active tracks\n|align=right|{{coord|32.64537|-85.38348|format=dms}}\n|-\n|[[Union Springs, Alabama|Union Springs]]\n|[[Alabama]]\n|[[Central of Georgia Railway]]\n|1925\n|Coaling tower\n|\n|[[Fairbanks-Morse]]\n|Similar to Raymond\n|align=right|{{coord|32.13956|-85.71523|format=dms}}\n|-\n|[[Osier, Colorado|Osier]]\n|[[Colorado]]\n|[[Cumbres and Toltec Scenic Railroad]]\n|\n|Coal dock\n|\n|\n|Active track\n|align=right|{{coord|37.01391|-106.33623|format=dms}}\n|-\n|Vance Junction\n|[