oader\n|\n|[[Fairbanks-Morse]]\n|Active tracks\n|align=right|{{coord|45.09195|-87.64288|format=dms}}\n|-\n|[[Montfort, Wisconsin|Montfort]]\n|[[Wisconsin]]\n|[[Chicago and North Western Transportation Company|Chicago and North Western Railway]]\n|\n|Coaling tower\n|\n|\n|Abandoned\n|align=right|{{coord|42.9637|-90.40871|format=dms}}\n|}\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Hornepayne ON 3.JPG|Hornepayne, Ontario\nFile:Roundhouse and coal tower Toronto 2013 greyscale.jpg|Toronto, Ontario\nFile:La carbonera.JPG|Temuco, Chile\nFile:Tarnowskie G\u00f3ry - elewator w\u0119glowy.jpg|Tarnowskie G\u00f3ry, Poland\nFile:SAR Class 25NC 3437 (4-8-4).JPG|SAR Class 25NC 3437 (4-8-4) at the coal stage at Beaconsfield, South Africa\nFile:Coaling Tower (disused) - geograph.org.uk - 653373.jpg|Carnforth, United Kingdom\nFile:Didcot railway centre coaling stage - geograph.org.uk - 990220.jpg|Didcot, United Kingdom\nFile:Former locomotive coaling stage, Immingham depot (geograph 3717022).jpg|Immingham, United Kingdom\nFile:Rusttoweron welton.jpg|Cedar Hill Yard, Connecticut\nFile:Found another of Roger Puta's slides of a Georgia RR mixed train, this time at Camak, Ga. in September 1964 with freight cars (25437547466).jpg|Camak, Georgia\nFile:Central of Gerogia Coal Tower and Chute.JPG|Macon, Georgia\nFile:Social Circle IMG 0217.JPG|Social Circle, Georgia\nFile:C&TS Chama Coaling-Tower 2012-10-24.JPG|Chama, New Mexico\nFile:An old coaling tower that once served Chesapeake & Ohio steam locomotives moving through Bluefield, West Virginia LCCN2015634388.tif|Bluefield, West Virginia\nFile:An old coaling tower that once served Chesapeake & Ohio locomotives moving through Hinton, West Virginia LCCN2015634368.tif|Hinton, West Virginia\nFile:Coal Tower - Thurmond, WV (1955332156).jpg|Thurmond, West Virginia\nFile:SSW 9641 Mescal AZ June 1993xRP - Flickr - drewj1946.jpg|Mescal, Arizona (demolished)\nFile:C&NW coaling station 1942.jpg|Locomotive 2576 over ash pit at the roundhouse and coaling station