ar/19/dystopian-films-blade-runner-insurgent-future-grim|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=14 June 2015|date=19 March 2015}}</ref><!--todo-->\n|-\n| ''[[Babylon A.D.]]''\n| 2008\n| Veteran-turned-mercenary Toorop takes the high-risk job of escorting a woman from Russia to America. Little does he know that she is host to an organism that a cult wants to harvest in order to produce a genetically modified Messiah.\n| <ref>{{cite book|title=GameAxis Unwired|date=September 2008|page=81|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tOoDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA81&dq=Babylon+A.D.+dystopia|accessdate=8 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Anders|first1=Charlie Jane|title=Finally, A Dystopia Grim Enough For Vin Diesel|url=http://io9.com/386259/finally-a-dystopia-grim-enough-for-vin-diesel|accessdate=8 June 2015|date=2008}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Batman (1989 film)|Batman]]''\n| 1989\n| Based on the [[DC Comics]] [[Batman|character of the same name]], directed by [[Tim Burton]]. Gotham City is a place overflowed by crime where a masked vigilante named Batman fights the crime. Trying to stop a stalk in Axis Chemicals, he causes unwittingly that a gangster, Jack Napier, falls into a tank of acid, turning him in the demented Joker.\n| <ref name=projecting>{{cite book|title=Projecting the End of the American Dream: Hollywood's Visions of U.S. Decline|first=Gordon B.|last=Arnold|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zavWAQAAQBAJ|publisher=ABC-CLIO|year=2013|isbn=9780313385643}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Battle Royale (film)|Battle Royale]]''\n| 2000\n| Based on [[Battle Royale (novel)|the novel]] and [[Battle Royale (manga)|manga]] of the same name.\n| <ref name=taste>{{cite web|work=Taste of Cinema|url=http://www.tasteofcinema.com/2014/20-great-dystopian-films-that-are-worth-your-time/|title=20 Great Dystopian Films That Are Worth Your Time|date=14 October 2014|first=Emilio|last=Santoni}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Battlefield Earth (film)|Battlefield Earth]]''\n| 2000\n| Film adaptation of [[L. Ron Hubbard]]'s 1982 nove