rimfuture/><ref name=wonttouch/><ref name=whyteens/><ref name=jstor/><ref name=freemarket>{{cite web|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2014/sep/01/ya-dystopias-children-free-market-hunger-games-the-giver-divergent|title=YA dystopias teach children to submit to the free market, not fight authority|first=Ewan|last=Morrison|date=1 September 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Handmaid's Tale (film)|The Handmaid's Tale]]''\n| 1990\n| Based on [[The Handmaid's Tale|the 1985 novel of the same name]] by [[Margaret Atwood]], in a dystopically polluted rightwing religious tyranny, a young woman is put in sexual slavery on account of her now rare fertility.\n| <ref name=tropes/><ref name=routledge/><ref name=freemarket/>\n|-\n| ''[[Hard to Be a God (2013 film)|Hard to be a God]]''\n| 2013\n| A group of 30 scientists travel from Earth to a nearly-identical alien planet that is culturally and technologically centuries behind. The inhabitants of this planet have brutally suppressed a renaissance movement, murdering anybody they consider to be an intellectual, and thus the planet is stuck in the Middle Ages.\n|<ref>{{cite web | last=Bradshaw | first=Peter | title=Hard to Be a God review \u2013 mud, blood and holy hell | website=the Guardian | date=2015-08-06 | url=http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/aug/06/hard-to-be-a-god-review-mud-blood-and-holy-hell | access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Hardware (film)|Hardware]]''\n| 1990\n| Inspired by the short story \"Shok!\" in 2000 AD (1980), the film depicts the rampage of a self-repairing robot in a post-apocalyptic slum.\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1990-09-17/entertainment/ca-458_1_blood-baths|work=LA Times|last=Wilmington|first=Michael|date=17 September 1990|title=Movie Reviews : 'Hardware': Relentless High-Tech Blood Bath}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Harrison Bergeron (film)|Harrison Bergeron]]''\n| 1995\n| A cable television movie adapted from the [[Harrison Bergeron|short story of the same name]]