-1200524627/|title=Review: 'The Island'|last=Chang|first=Justin|date=10 July 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=Sacramento News and Review|title=The Island|last=Lane|first=Jim|date=21 July 2005|url=http://www.newsreview.com/sacramento/island/content?oid=39012}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[La Jet\u00e9e]]''\n| 1962\n| In the aftermath of World War III scientists in Paris research time travel, hoping to send test subjects to different time periods \"to call past and future to the rescue of the present\". The short film by [[Chris Marker]] was constructed almost entirely from still photos and inspired the 1995 film ''[[12 Monkeys (film)|12 Monkeys]]''.\n| <ref name=10best>{{cite news|last1=Monae|first1=Janelle|title=The 10 best Dystopias|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2014/aug/08/the-10-best-dystopias|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=14 June 2015|date=8 August 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Franck|first1=Katharina|title=\"The future is a thing of the past\" - Untersuchungen zur Geschichte des dystopischen Films|date=2010|url=http://othes.univie.ac.at/10068/1/2010-05-27_0547917.pdf|accessdate=14 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dystopischer Jugendfilm|url=http://www2.mediamanual.at/pdf/filmabc/55_filmabc_Dystopien.pdf|publisher=f!lmABC|accessdate=14 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Mavor|first1=Carol|authorlink=Carol Mavor|title=Black and Blue: The Bruising Passion of ''Camera Lucida, La Jet\u00e9e, Sans soleil, and Hiroshima mon amour''|date=2012|isbn=978-0-8223-5271-6|page=60|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OiFkvwzEoGsC&pg=PA60&dq=La+Jet\u00e9e+dystopia+-critical|accessdate=14 June 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Johnny Mnemonic (film)|Johnny Mnemonic]]''\n| 1995\n| Based on the 1981 short story of the same name by William Gibson, in which a data courier, literally carrying a data package inside his head, must deliver it before he dies from the burden or is killed by the Yakuza.\n\n| <ref>{{cite web|last=Harmon|first=Amy|work=LA Times|date=24 May 1995|t