iet-steampunk/|date=26 January 2008|last=Ebb|first=Zoetica}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Land of the Blind]]''\n| 2006\n| A dark political satire, based on several incidents throughout history in which tyrannical rulers were overthrown by new leaders who proved to be just as bad, if not worse, and subtle references are made to several such cases.\n| <ref name=prophecy/>\n|-\n| ''[[The Last Man on Earth (1964 film)|The Last Man on Earth]]''\n| 1964\n| The first of three adaptations of [[Richard Matheson]]'s 1954 novel ''[[I Am Legend (novel)|I Am Legend]]''. A scientist tries to survive in an apocalyptic world where a global disease turned human in vampires.\n| <ref name=gaze/>\n|-\n| ''[[The Lego Movie]]''\n| 2014\n| Animation based on the Lego line of construction toys, tells the story of an ordinary Lego minifigure as he ends up becoming involved in a resistance against a tyrannical businessman who plans to glue everything in the Lego worlds.\n| <ref name=TVnews/><ref name=legomedium>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/message/a-fun-stopia-for-todays-busy-citizen-ce8488d27064|work=The Message|last=Norton|first=Quinn|date=31 July 2014|title=A Fun-Stopia for Today's Busy Citizen:Examining 'The Lego Movie' as a sequel to the 1921 dystopian novel 'We'}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=Under the Radar|url=http://www.undertheradarmag.com/reviews/the_lego_movie/|title=The Lego Movie|date=5 February 2014|last=Trunick|first=Austin}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Lobster]]''\n| 2015\n| Somewhere in the near future, single people face a choice: join a program to find a mate in forty-five days or be transformed into an animal.\n| <ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_lobster/|title = Rotten Tomatoes Lobster Page}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Logan's Run (film)|Logan's Run]]''\n| 1976\n| Depicts a dystopian future society set in 2274 in which population and the consumption of resources are managed by the simple notion of killing everyone who reaches the age of thirty.\n| <ref name=tropes/><ref n