ned based on [[computational model]]s and [[quantitative structure-activity relationship|QSAR]] studies.<ref name=\"pmid12668005\">{{cite journal |vauthors=L\u00f3pez-Rodr\u00edguez ML, Morcillo MJ, Fern\u00e1ndez E | title = Design and synthesis of S-(\u2212)-2-<nowiki>[[</nowiki>4-(napht-1-yl)piperazin-1-yl]methyl]-1,4-dioxoperhydropyrrolo[1,2-a]pyrazine (CSP-2503) using computational simulation. A 5-HT1A receptor agonist | journal = Bioorganic & Medicinal Chemistry Letters | volume = 13 | issue = 8 | pages = 1429\u201332 |date=April 2003 | pmid = 12668005 | doi = 10.1016/S0960-894X(03)00160-4|display-authors=etal}}</ref><ref name=\"pmid15801844\">{{cite journal |vauthors=L\u00f3pez-Rodr\u00edguez ML, Morcillo MJ, Fern\u00e1ndez E | title = Synthesis and structure-activity relationships of a new model of arylpiperazines. 8. Computational simulation of ligand-receptor interaction of 5-HT(1A)R agonists with selectivity over alpha1-adrenoceptors | journal = Journal of Medicinal Chemistry | volume = 48 | issue = 7 | pages = 2548\u201358 |date=April 2005 | pmid = 15801844 | doi = 10.1021/jm048999e |display-authors=etal}}</ref> In rat studies, CSP-2503 has demonstrated [[anxiolytic]] effects, and thus has been suggested as a treatment for [[anxiety]] in humans with a multimodal [[mechanism of action]].<ref name=\"pmid15777774\"/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Naphthylpiperazine]]\n* [[S-14,671]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Anxiolytics}}\n{{Serotonergics}}\n{{Piperazines}}\n\n[[Category:Diketopiperazines]]\n[[Category:Pyrrolopyrazines]]\n[[Category:Lactams]]\n[[Category:Experimental drugs]]\n[[Category:Naphthylpiperazines]]\n", "text_old": "{{Drugbox\n| verifiedrevid = 414040667\n| IUPAC_name = 2-[(4-naphthalen-1-ylpiperazin-1-yl)methyl]hexahydropyrrolo[1,2-a]pyrazine-1,4-dione\n| image = CSP-2503-structure.png\n\n<!--Clinical data-->\n| tradename =  \n| pregnancy_category =  \n| legal_status =  \n| routes_of_administration =\n\n<!--Pharmacokinetic data-->\n| bioavail